            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a fan of raw garlic? Try using less!) in a bowl with the <strong>chopped dill</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> [1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your <strong>herby aioli</strong></p>",
