          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658226067252-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1658226067252-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, pat your <strong>hake fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and cut in half widthways</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a plate and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cornflour mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>hake pieces</strong> to the plate and press them into the <strong>cornflour mix</strong> until completely coated – this is your <strong>coated hake</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658226070951-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658226070951-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658226070951-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658226070951-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1658226070951-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated hake</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through and lightly crisped – this is your <strong>crispy hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1658226074835-x200.jpg",
